commit.message:
Expand CitiBike MLOps guide: Purpose/Tasks per phase, time series methods, Phases 5-10

- Phase 3: Proper baselines (EB formula, NegBin GLM, seasonal naive, Prophet);
  overdispersion check; consistent run structure with poisson_deviance helper
- Phase 4: Walk-forward CV with leakage guard assertion; MASE metric;
  directional accuracy; Durbin-Watson residual test; decile calibration plot;
  spatial holdout (20% of stations); concrete model selection criteria
- Phase 5: Full promote_if_better() with MLflow client comparison logic;
  min_improvement threshold; structured model card template
- Phase 6: Daily feature cache pattern for inference-time lag features;
  cold-start fallback for new stations; build_risk_features_at_inference();
  cold_start flag in RiskResponse schema
- Phase 7: Temporal drift awareness (compare same period last year, not
  rolling baseline, to avoid seasonal false positives)
- Phase 8: Full wired DAG (drift → ingest → features → train → promote →
  cache); DRY promote_if_better reuse; feature cache always refreshed
- Phase 9: Cross-station leakage test; TimeSeriesSplit ordering test;
  cold-start API test; invalid input 422 test
- Phase 10 (new): Quantile regression PIs; conformal prediction; hierarchical
  forecasting; DIRECT multi-step; weather exogenous via Open-Meteo
- Updated summary checklist (54 items covering Phases 0-10)

